version: 0.2.0
name: cute_robot_component_sheet_greenscreen
description: Rough component atlas metadata for a green-screen robot component sheet.
  Run refine before slicing; rough boxes are approximate and corrected with green-screen
  foreground connected-component analysis.
image:
  file: ../assets/robot_components_greenscreen.png
  size:
  - 1448
  - 1086
  background: greenscreen
  background_color_hint: '#09F50D'
  coordinate_system: pixels_top_left
  units: px
metadata_quality:
  rect_precision: rough_approximate
  pivot_precision: draft_approximate
  anchor_precision: draft_approximate
  workflow:
  - Author or generate rough boxes in this YAML.
  - Run refine to locate actual foreground components inside each rough search window.
  - Run slice on refined metadata to extract each sprite and key out the greenscreen.
  - Use contact-sheet to visually QA extracted components.
  notes:
  - Rough boxes are intentionally padded but avoid containing neighboring component
    centers.
  - The refinement step selects connected foreground components using the green-screen
    mask, then shrinks/expands to a padded true extent.
  - HIT is recoil/stagger only and must not be generated as a death pose.
  - TELEPORT replaces the old blink action; blink remains a face expression only.
refinement:
  source: rough_yaml
  default_search_padding: 8
  output_padding: 4
  background_estimate: median_border_color
  background_distance_transparent: 38
  background_distance_opaque: 92
  component_selection:
    center_inside_rough_rect: true
    min_component_area: 18
    min_overlap_fraction: 0.18
    keep_multiple_components: true
  despill_green: true
  warnings:
  - warn when no foreground is found
  - warn when selected foreground touches the search-window boundary
  - warn when a refined crop nearly touches a neighboring component
  clamp_points_to_crop: true
style:
  character: cute white cartoon robot
  linework: thick rounded black outline with clean inked silhouette
  shading: soft cel-shaded highlights, no painterly smudging
  palette:
    body: '#f7f7f2'
    visor: '#0b0f12'
    eyes: '#00eaff'
    accent_purple: '#a55cff'
    joint_dark: '#202326'
    effect_cyan: '#33eaff'
    effect_purple: '#9d4dff'
  rendering_rules:
  - preserve thick black outline
  - keep shapes rounded and toy-like
  - avoid hard mechanical angles
  - avoid blurry/smudged edges
  - avoid text inside production sprite sheets
  - use cyan glow only for eyes, teleport, dash, and hit particles
  - use purple energy primarily for slash/weapon effects
generator_instructions:
  purpose: Guide an image generator or procedural compositor when using these robot
    components as reusable parts.
  high_level_rule: Use these elements as a clean design vocabulary. The rig may transform
    parts for pose, but final animation frames may be beautified/redrawn to preserve
    the polished AI-generated look.
  positive_prompt: polished cute white cartoon robot, thick clean black outlines,
    cyan glowing digital eyes, purple antenna and accents, rounded toy-like proportions,
    crisp sprite component, consistent lighting, solid green-screen or transparent
    background, centered reusable game asset
  negative_prompt: blurry, smudged, painterly, distorted, warped text, fake labels,
    inconsistent proportions, messy outlines, low resolution, grungy, over-detailed
    mechanical parts, death pose for hit reaction
  composition_rules:
  - Do not generate labels, timing text, frame numbers, or grid lines inside final
    sprites.
  - Keep each component centered in its crop with enough padding for rotation.
  - Maintain matching line weight across head, body, limbs, antenna, and effects.
  - Use deterministic code for final atlas layout, spacing, labels, and frame timing
    metadata.
  - Prefer a single solid green-screen background when alpha is unavailable so the
    slicer can remove it deterministically.
